=begin pod
=head2 set-default-sort-func

B<Note: The native version of this routine is deprecated in gtk4-lib() since version 4.10>

Sets the default comparison function used when sorting to be C<$sort-func>.
If the current sort column id of C<$sortable> is
C<GTK_TREE_SORTABLE_DEFAULT_SORT_COLUMN_ID>, then the model will sort using
this function.

If C<$sort-func> is undefined, then there will be no default comparison function.
This means that once the model  has been sorted, it canâ€™t go back to the
default state. In this case, when the current sort column id of C<$sortable>
is C<GTK_TREE_SORTABLE_DEFAULT_SORT_COLUMN_ID>, the model will be unsorted.

=begin code
method set-default-sort-func ( GtkTreeIterCompareFunc &sort-func, gpointer $user-data, GDestroyNotify &destroy )
=end code

=item GtkTreeIterCompareFunc &sort-func; The comparison function. The function must be specified with the following signature; C<:( N-Object $model, N-Object $a, N-Object $b, gpointer $user-data )>.
=item $user-data; User data to pass to C<$sort-func>.
=item GDestroyNotify &destroy; Destroy notifier of C<$user-data>. The function must be specified with the following signature; C<:( gpointer $data )>.

