=begin pod
=head2 set-sort-func

B<Note: The native version of this routine is deprecated in gtk4-lib() since version 4.10>

Sets the comparison function used when sorting to be C<$sort-func>. If the
current sort column id of C<$sortable> is the same as C<$sort-column-id>, then
the model will sort using this function.

=begin code
method set-sort-func ( Int() $sort-column-id, GtkTreeIterCompareFunc &sort-func, gpointer $user-data, GDestroyNotify &destroy )
=end code

=item $sort-column-id; the sort column id to set the function for.
=item GtkTreeIterCompareFunc &sort-func; The comparison function. The function must be specified with the following signature; C<:( N-Object $model, N-Object $a, N-Object $b, gpointer $user-data )>.
=item $user-data; User data to pass to C<$sort-func>.
=item GDestroyNotify &destroy; Destroy notifier of C<$user-data>. The function must be specified with the following signature; C<:( gpointer $data )>.

